pr_review_comment_body:
can we use json syntax here so `/path/to/file` should be json strings:

```json
{
    "exclude": [
        "path/to/file",
        "path/to/files/ignore_*.py
    }
}
```

This vector is really only needed in the local inhibition case. Maybe it'd be better to do the boostFactor computation in two places, and avoid creating this vector every time step in the "global inhibition" case?

In other words, there will be two different lines:

~~~c++
// Global inhibition
Real boostFactor = exp(-(activeDutyCycles_[i] - density) * maxBoost_);

// Local inhibition
Real boostFactor = exp(-(activeDutyCycles_[i] - targetDensity[i]) * maxBoost_);
 ~~~

@yashu-seth You will have to do something like this:
```python
def reduce(state, inplace=True):
    def reduced_pdf(a, b, d):
        return self.pdf(a, b, c=state, d)
    self.pdf = reduced_pdf

def product(factor2, inplace=False):
     def new_pdf(a, b, c, d):
         return self.pdf(a, b, c) * factor2.pdf(b, c, d)
     return ContinuousFactor(variables=self.variables \union factor2.variables, pdf=new_pdf)
```

